# Template for consuming/publishing this package via a Foundry first-party npm registry.
# Copy to `.npmrc` and fill in your values. Do NOT commit the real `.npmrc` (it is gitignored).
#
# 1. Replace <SCOPE> with your Foundry npm scope (e.g. @your-org).
# 2. Replace <REGISTRY_URL> with the FIRST-PARTY Foundry npm registry URL
#    (NOT the read-only external mirror "external-npm-npmjs").
#    It looks roughly like:
#    https://<stack>.palantirfoundry.com/artifacts/api/repositories/<repo-rid>/contents/release/npm
# 3. Provide the token via an environment variable rather than hardcoding it.

@<SCOPE>:registry=<REGISTRY_URL>
//<REGISTRY_HOST>/...:_authToken=${FOUNDRY_NPM_TOKEN}
